members.name: isOnline
members.comment: Checks if this player is currently online

members.name: getName
members.comment: Returns the name of this player Names are no longer unique past a single game session. For persistent storage it is recommended that you use getUniqueId() instead.

return: Player name or null if we have not seen a name for this player yet

members.name: getUniqueId
members.comment: Returns the UUID of this player

members.name: isBanned
members.comment: Checks if this player is banned or not

members.name: isWhitelisted
members.comment: Checks if this player is whitelisted or not

members.name: setWhitelisted
members.comment: Sets if this player is whitelisted or not

members.name: getPlayer
members.comment: Gets a Player object that this represents, if there is one If the player is online, this will return that player. Otherwise, it will return null.

members.name: getFirstPlayed
members.comment: Gets the first date and time that this player was witnessed on this server. If the player has never played before, this will return 0. Otherwise, it will be the amount of milliseconds since midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC.

return: Date of first log-in for this player, or 0

members.name: getLastPlayed
members.comment: Gets the last date and time that this player was witnessed on this server. If the player has never played before, this will return 0. Otherwise, it will be the amount of milliseconds since midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC.

return: Date of last log-in for this player, or 0

members.name: hasPlayedBefore
members.comment: Checks if this player has played on this server before.

return: True if the player has played before, otherwise false

members.name: getBedSpawnLocation
members.comment: Gets the Location where the player will spawn at their bed, null if they have not slept in one or their current bed spawn is invalid.

return: Bed Spawn Location if bed exists, otherwise null.

members.name: incrementStatistic
members.comment: Increments the given statistic for this player. This is equivalent to the following code: incrementStatistic(Statistic, 1)

throws: IllegalArgumentException - if statistic is null
IllegalArgumentException - if the statistic requires an additional parameter

members.name: decrementStatistic
members.comment: Decrements the given statistic for this player. This is equivalent to the following code: decrementStatistic(Statistic, 1)
